[1] I think that it is a very good initiative. The SDGs also state that everyone should have access to toilets. In particular, the smell of sewage is so bad in developing countries. I had often heard about the problem of people getting sick because of lack of toilets in other classes at university. However, in some cultures, some people consider it rude to mix their own poop with someone’s poop by using the toilet. Therefore, I do not think it is a good idea to force everyone in the world to use toilets. And I can not drink purified water made from excrement because I know it is made from poop. note 1 toilet 2 several hundred million 3 muffin 4 water 5 Billions of people do not have them The wastewater treatment plant Working with Nasa                                      
[2] I was surprised that there are microbes eating poop and turning it into clean water. I can’t agree with Bill Gates’s behaviour of carrying a jar of his own shit because it may make many people disgusted. But, the project of turning excrement into clean water is a very good idea in terms of water shortage and preventing diseases. However, if I knew the origin of this water, I wouldn't want to drink it. So I think there is a risk of denying drinking it. Compared to this water fact, I think turning excrement into energy is very important. I think it is the most efficient way. But, there is also the big risk, global warming. Methane, resource the microbes can make, is the big cause of global warming. So being able to make energy is very amazing, but there is too much risk.
[3] I was surprised to hear about Bill Gates’ idea to make a toilet which doesn’t need a sewer system. And also I thought it is a very good idea to help developing countries, because of the reasons why poor people die. Dirty water causes people diarrhea. According to Unicef, “Approximately 60 percent of infant deaths due to diarrhea are related to dirty water and unsanitary environments.” So dirty water kills a lot of children and adults. If Bill Gates is able to make a toilet which doesn’t need a sewer system, the water will be more clean, and people will survive better than before.                                                                                                                                                                                                 
[4] The news uses humor to talk about the serious issue of sanitation. I think the idea of turning poop into clean water and energy is good. I’m impressed that someone as rich as Bill Gates is working on such an important problem.
